R. L. GATES et al. v. MISSOURI-KANSAS-TEXAS RAILROAD COMPANY et al. No. 1225. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Oct. 30, 1935. Stuart, Bell & Ledbetter and E. E. Blake, all of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellants. R. B. F. Hummer and M. D. Green, both of Oklahoma City, Okl., and Fred M. Carter, of Bartlesville, Okl., for appellees.

Before LEWIS, PHILLIPS, and McDERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed, on stipulation.
